# API Modules Guide

The Nexla SDK is organized into API modules, each handling a specific area of the Nexla platform.

## Base API

- [nexla_sdk/api/base.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/base.py) - Base API class with common functionality for all API modules

## Resource-specific APIs

- [nexla_sdk/api/flows.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/flows.py) - API for Nexla Flows management
- [nexla_sdk/api/sources.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/sources.py) - API for managing data sources
- [nexla_sdk/api/destinations.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/destinations.py) - API for managing data destinations
- [nexla_sdk/api/transforms.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/transforms.py) - API for data transformations
- [nexla_sdk/api/nexsets.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/nexsets.py) - API for Nexla datasets management
- [nexla_sdk/api/credentials.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/credentials.py) - API for credentials management
- [nexla_sdk/api/lookups.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/lookups.py) - API for Data Maps (Lookups) management

## Organizational APIs

- [nexla_sdk/api/projects.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/projects.py) - API for managing projects
- [nexla_sdk/api/teams.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/teams.py) - API for teams management
- [nexla_sdk/api/organizations.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/organizations.py) - API for organizations management
- [nexla_sdk/api/users.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/users.py) - API for user management

## Additional APIs

- [nexla_sdk/api/webhooks.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/webhooks.py) - API for webhook integrations
- [nexla_sdk/api/metrics.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/metrics.py) - API for metrics collection
- [nexla_sdk/api/notifications.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/notifications.py) - API for notifications management
- [nexla_sdk/api/audit_logs.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/audit_logs.py) - API for audit logging
- [nexla_sdk/api/access.py](mdc:nexla_sdk/api/access.py) - API for access control management
